ili9341
========
A Raspberry pi framebuffer driver for the ili9341 lcd driver.
I am using the NHD-2.4-240320SF-CTXI#-T1 (http://www.newhavendisplay.com/nhd24240320sfctxit1-p-3975.html)

**Version 2.0 - Modernized for Raspberry Pi Zero 2W and recent kernels**

This driver has been updated to support modern Raspberry Pi models including:
- Raspberry Pi Zero 2W
- Raspberry Pi 3/4
- Recent Linux kernels (5.x, 6.x)
- Dynamic GPIO base address detection via Device Tree


NHD-2.4-240320SF-CTXI#-T1 Datasheet (http://www.newhavendisplay.com/specs/NHD-2.4-240320SF-CTXI-T1.pdf)
ili9341 Datasheet (http://www.displayfuture.com/Display/datasheet/controller/ILI9341.pdf)

Installing:
   download the source
   run make
   sudo insmod ili9341.ko
this will create /dev/fb1.
Use the new framebuffer (https://github.com/notro/fbtft/wiki/Framebuffer-use)

Building:
   make                      # Build kernel module
   make clean                # Clean build artifacts
   make dtbo                 # Build Device Tree overlay
   make all-with-overlay     # Build both module and overlay
   sudo make install         # Install module (or use make load to auto-load)
   sudo make uninstall       # Remove module

Improvements in v2.0:
   - Dynamic GPIO base address detection from Device Tree
   - Automatic Raspberry Pi model detection
   - Support for Pi Zero 2W, Pi 3, Pi 4
   - Kernel version compatibility checking
   - Device Tree overlay support for hardware configuration
   - Improved error handling and logging


The physical part of things.

